procstep.procdesc: 1. The Site boundary is defined by the DER Project Manager when a site is added to any of the Department's remediation programs. 2. DER staff add provide the spatial information to DER's tracking system database. 3. All other attributes are imported from DER's tracking system database, based on the Site ID 4. The Site Boundary is reviewed at critical steps during the investigation and remediation process and updated as necessary. 5. The SDE feature class is updated nightly from a DER file geodatabase, and attributes from the DER Remediation Site point feature class is joined into the polygon feature class.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: The Site Code (a.k.a. Site ID No., Site Number) is the Registry number assigned by the NYSDEC. The first digit represents the NYSDEC Region in which the site is located, the next two digits represent the county, and the final three digits designate the particular site within the county. Some sites bear a letter following the final three digits. Site Codes which include a letter following the six digit number are known by the entire string.
The Site Name is the formal name of the site as assigned by the NYSDEC.
The Division of Environmental Remediation Program under which the site is being investigated and/or cleaned up. Additional information can be found at http://www.dec.ny.gov/about/627.html .

attrdomv.udom: Please see Cross References for "Brownfield Cleanup Program", "State Superfund Program", "Environmental Restoration Program", and "Voluntary Cleanup Program".

attr.attrdef: The Site Class record is the site's classification according to the Hazardous Waste Site Classification System. Site classifications of 1, 2, 3, 4, or 5 only apply to sites being remediated under the State Superfund Program and indicates the degree of threat and the status of the site in the remedial process. Site classifications of C or A apply to the other Division Programs - Environmental Restoration Program, Voluntary Cleanup Program, and Brownfield Cleanup Program.

edom.edomvd: Causing or presenting an imminent danger of causing irreversible or irreparable damage to the public health or environment - immediate action required.
Significant threat to the public health or environment - action required.
Does not present a significant threat to the public health or the environment - action may be deferred.
Site properly closed - requires continued management.
Site properly closed, no evidence of present or potential adverse impact - no further action is required.
Active: Classification to be used for non-Registry sites in any remedial program where work is underway and not yet complete (i.e. BCP, ERP, VCP sites).

Remediation Complete (formerly D2): Used for sites in any remedial program where the Department has determined that remediation has been satisfactorily completed. This can include delisted Registry sites and non-Registry sites that have satisfactorily completed construction and are eligible to receive a Certificate of Completion. Note that complete sites may still require some degree of site management associated with either operation, maintenance, and monitoring or with institutional/engineering controls (IC/ECs).

attr.attrdef: Street address for the site's location.
Street address for the site's location.
City, town or village where the site is located.
ZIP CODE for the site's address.
The region number corresponds to one of the nine NYSDEC regions in which the site is located.
NYTM x coordinate of site centroid
